text:
Even though it might be a struggle I will try my best to explain the inspiration behind my choice to pursue Info-Com through college.
When I was slightly younger, about 10 or 12 years old, I watched a movie called Alex Dupont I believe. It is about a horrendously intelligent woman who works for an anti-gun lobby company.
She is able to convince politicians to vote for an anti-gun law and always knows what those against her are about to do, she is always 5 moves forward. This fictional character impressed me from the very first time I saw this movie.
Maybe the link between this film and my field of study is a bit foreign for now but I will get to it.
Since then I have had the idea of becoming a lobbyist. However, even though it is still an option, I don't think that's what I want to become now. I do be impressed by the art of manipulating a conscience but I would like my job to be a bit more subtle. This is where communication studies come in. Learning how to communicate is very useful to understand how you can manipulate or convince someone. Communicating is also what allows you to create and build relationships. As would say the school of Palo Alto 'We can not not communicate. Knowing that it seems obvious that communication studies would help me with anything, any work-related or personal things I would like to pursue and execute.
Here is how I came to the decision of studying Information Communication here in Paris 2.
Since beginning my studies I realised I would love to work in the cultural world. I am moving to and fro between working as an editor, working in a theatre or doing communication work for a ballet company. I believe that both would fit me quite well indeed. My books' appetite might serve the first one whereas my love for dance and ballet would help with the two last ones.
I am pretty sure that choosing those studies was the right path for me, so I am glad I made this decision.
 This webpage performs keylogging of input typed into a textbox. In other words, when focused on the textbook below, the page will record each time you hit a key or select text with your mouse. All of the data is stored locally on your machine in the DOM and is downloadable as a JSON file. More information, about the motivation of this project and the format of the produced data are available here.
